comment: State Line Liquors selection from 2016, aged 9 years, 7 months. Very good!
Oesk is usually my favorite of all the yeast strains at Barrel strength.  Smooth oak forward profile.
A lot of heat, but faint woodiness.

The Wine and Cheese Place pick
Barrel 31.2J
10 years 4 months
56.4% abv

Surprisingly subtle, substantial rye spice for the E mashbill, dense in texture with some dark chocolate, tarragon, marjoram, rather dry and really needs time to open up
